items.title: Is it possible to get a higher dimensional tensor as a result of `map_fn()`?
items.body:
I need to look through the tensor elements and replace them by 1d tensor like in this toy example:

m = tf.range(0, my_range)
res = tf.map_fn(fn=lambda t: [t], elems=m)

But I am getting an exception:

Exception has occurred: ValueError The two structures don't have the same nested structure.
